According to The PUNCH, the Senate President, Ahmad Lawan, on Wednesday, referred the N895, 842,465,917.00 Supplementary Budget meant to tackle insecurity and health-related issues to the Committee on Appropriation.  Lawan, who gave the directive after the supplementary appropriation passed second reading on the floor of the Senate, asked the Senator Barau Jibrin-led panel to submit its report on Tuesday next week. The report of the panel would be submitted, considered, and passed the same day. The President, Major General Muhammdu Buhari (retd.), had on Tuesday transmitted the document to the National Assembly for consideration and approval. Details later.. Abuja - The National Assembly on Tuesday said it would not go back on its position on the 2016 Appropriation Bill. Spokesperson of the Senate, Dr Abdullahi Sabi, told newsmen in Abuja that the 1999 Constitution had made provision for a supplementary appropriation in the event of omissions in the… In "Politics" By Cecilia Ijuo Abuja  -   The Senate on Thursday, failed to lay the 2017 Appropriation Bill in plenary, contrary to its promise to Nigerians that the bill would be passed before Friday. The tenure of the 2016 Appropriation Act would end on Friday. Against expectations, the Leader of the Senate,… In "Top Stories" ….Seeks Support Of ICAN In Ensuring Accountability and Transparency on Agencies Tasked with Revenue Generation, Collection And Remittance By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) - President of the Senate, Ahmad Lawan, on Tuesday, assured Nigerians that both chambers of the National Assembly might pass the 2020 Budget next week Wednesday.… In "Top Stories"